foia:OldestPendingRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: The FOIA tracking system indicates the numbers in red are accurate. The dates are in date order, but the pending days are not. This is likely because the clock was stopped at some point.

OIG Appeals - Costs are for the OIG only.

foia:BacklogSection.foia:FootnoteText: There was a small increase in the number of backlogged requests for the agency overall for FY 10 (31) vs. FY09 (28). This slight increase in the number is attributable to two items. 1) The USPS processed a number of complex requests in FY 10. The processing of these requests required coordination with a number of records custodians at National Headquarters and at field offices. 2) The Records Office physically moved its office location. The USPS Records Office was administratively closed for a two-week period during the move.

foia:ProcessedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: USPIS and OIG reported as one agency component (JLSC) for FY09. USPIS and OIG reported as separate agency components for FY 10.
